node.text:
Today’s Update…
Can & Crowler Release at both spots!
• • • • • • • • •
American For Pale - Hoppy Pale Ale w/ Citra, Strata & Mosaic, 5.4% abv
Our 3rd batch of this one brings us to our favorite spot yet! Vibrant and hoppy throughout, with a delicate kiss of malt across its medium body, and showing off hoppy aromatic layers of nectarine skin, fresh strawberries, and Oro Blanco grapefruit. $11 per Crowler (32oz)
• • • • • • • • •
Australian For Pale - Hoppy Pale Ale w/ Motueka, Galaxy & Nelson, 5.8% abv
This super hoppy pale ale gets hit in the boil and the dry hop with some of our favorite Southern Hemisphere hops; Galaxy, Motueka & Nelson. The malt flavor is almost non-existent with the flavor profile only showcasing these hoppy beauties. The lime flavor pops the most, with peach rings and mango trailing behind. 2019 Gold Medal winner at the Great American Beer Festival in the Australian-style Pale Ale category. $15 per 4pack. No limit.
• • • • • • • • •
Come pay us a visit in Orange! We’ve now got our tasting room open 7 days a week, as well as our little Drive-Thru too. We’ve got our own food being served Wednesday through Sunday, with a “bring your own food” thing going on Mondays & Tuesdays. Check greencheekbeer.com for those up to date hours.
• • • • • • • • •
Our Costa Mesa spot @greencheekbeertoo is open for onsite eating/drinking everyday of the week, inside and out! Hours are 11am to 10pm Sunday - Wednesday, and then 11am to 11pm on Thursday - Saturday.
• • • • • • • • •
Our new Last Call / Closing Time policy has changed! You may now get a drink up until the posted closing time. If we say that the closing time is at 11pm, you may still buy beer till 11pm! It’s that simple.

Today’s Update…
Fresh cans and draft of this summertime crusher is back at both spots!

Here We Are - Belgian-style White Ale w/ California Oranges & Coriander, 5.0% abv
Using Raw Wheat, Pilsner Malt, old fashioned oats, and then fermented with an estery Belgian yeast. We finished it off with fresh ground coriander and house made dried orange peel from locally grown Navel Oranges. The result is a thirst quencher and definitely a reminder to us of how much we love this beer style! The spice and zest are present, but without trampling all over the expressive yeast. $14 per 4pack. No limit.

New Adventures // Nitro Golden Milk Stout - Collab w/ @portolacoffee - 5.4% abv
We teamed up with our bud, Jeff Duggan of Portola Coffee, to bring you something that looks like a blonde ale, but tastes like a coffee milk stout! It’s full-bodied, creamy like a Portola cappuccino, and hits with flavors of fresh baked chocolate chip cookies, toasted almonds, and coffee, yep, lots of coffee! Each can is ON NITRO, so you’ll want to give it a light shake for 30 seconds, let it rest for 30 seconds, crack it open, and then pour fast, down the side of your pint glass. *contains lactose* $18 per 4pack. No Limit.

Don’t Wake Me Up - DDH Hazy Triple IPA w/ Citra, Strata & Mosaic. 10.2% abv
Our highest rated beer on @untappd makes its return! Double dry hopped with Citra and then hit with equal parts Mosaic and Strata. Raw wheat and old fashioned oats help create the base, but it’s really all about the hops for this one. Milky yellow in color, with flavorful hoppy layers of passionfruit, guava, and kumquat. $24 per 4pack. Limit 4pp.

You've Got Pale - Collab w/ @cellarmakerbrewing , @pinthouse, @cloudburstbrew and @highlandparkbrewery - Cellarmaker-style Pale Ale w/ Citra, Strata & Amarillo, 5.6% abv
We got together with some of our best buds in the industry, and we all brewed Tim’s signature Cellarmaker-style Pale Ale. Each version of this beer from these five different breweries all use Citra, with the other hops being used, literally being pulled out of a hat by Tim, and represent what these brewers would consider an “old school” and a “new school” hop. Pouring a hazy yellow, and full of all the fresh hoppy aromatics and flavor that we love about those Cellarmaker pale ales, this one just sings with bright flavors of Melon Hi-Chew, Orange Sherbet, and Limon 7 packets. $16 per 4pack. No limit

node.text:
Today’s Update!
Double Can Release! New hats!! Our Online Beer Shop is Open!!!
• • • • • • • • •
Wait, Did You Print Out The Directions? - A West Coast IPA w/ Citra, Mosaic & Strata, 7.0% abv
The days of Mapquest may be long gone, but luckily for us West Coast IPA is here to stay! Our newest iteration uses a mix of Golden Promise and Pilsner malts to create just a touch of breadiness. It gets hop bursted with Ekuanot Cryo in the kettle, and then dry hopped with our hand selected lots of Citra, Mosaic, and Strata. The result is so fresh smelling, with a big hit of Oro Blanco zest, candied orange, and a bit of pine in the finish.
• • • • • • • • • Mouth Peace - German-style Pilsner, 5.0% abv
Modeled after Bavarian-style Pils, this dry lager bier is a lesson in patience for our brewers, as we wait for its edges to soften during the lagering period, and become more nuanced and quaffable. Delicately hoppy, with a firm bitterness, and a pleasant dryness that carries all the way through into the lingering finish.
• • • • • • • • •
New Hats! That 5 Panel Hat is $25, and that SnapBack w/ Cheeky is $30. Available at both spots and online.

node.text:
Today’s update!
Today marks our 4th Birthday here at GC, so we’re celebrating with a Triple Can Release!
• • • • • • • • •
It’s My BDAY Gift To Me! - Super Vanilla Imperial Pastry Stout Conditioned On Vanilla Beans from Comoros, Congo, Indonesia, Madagascar, Mexico, Papua New Guinea, Sri Lanka, Tanzania, Uganda & Vanuatu! 13.2% abv
Our 4th Birthday gift to ourselves! Made with a range of different malted, caramelized and roasted English barley for that base, reduced down in the kettle for 12 hours, and then lovingly conditioned on Vanilla Beans from 10 different countries until just right. A vegan beer. $16 per 16oz can. Limit 4pp.
• • • • • • • • •
DDH The Other Brian - DDH Hazy DIPA w/ 100% Citra, 8.5% abv
Our favorite hazy double returns and gets double dry hopped with lots of Citra! The hops take center stage and hit with flavors of ripe mango, fresh squeezed orange juice, and pineapple candy too. $22 per 4pack. Limit 4pp.
• • • • • • • • •
Power Band - Extra Passionfruit Super Berliner, 9.0% abv
A ginormous Berliner Weisse, that gets super’d to 2.5 times it’s normal strength and then hit with extra Passionfruit puree. The result is a beer that hits with all the fresh Passionfruit character  that your little heart could desire. The body is medium, with a pleasant hit of acidity, and sour peach rings vibes on the palate. $22 per 4pack. Limit 4pp.
• • • • • • • • •
Insanely grateful to all of our customers and staff for these past 4 years. Much love friends ❤️ - Evan & Brian
• • • • • • • • •

Today’s Update!
Double Can release at Both Spots!
• • • • • • • • •
Just One Thing...El Dorado! - DDH Hazy DIPA w/ El Dorado, 8.7% abv
It’s our little series of beers highlighting the extremes of one single hop variety, double dry hopped to overload the senses with all of what it is. We got our hands on a pretty special lot of El Dorado from @cls_farms (thanks Alex) that just sings in this one, and explodes with a flavor profile of Langers Mango Nectar, Fruity Pebbles, and Orange Juice. The finish is just too smooth. $22 per 4pack. Limit 4pp.
• • • • • • • • •
Wherever You Go - DDH Hazy IPA w/ Motueka & Citra, 7.0% abv
Made with a mountain of old fashioned oats, we keep this thing as light in color as we can before it’s double dry hopped. Milky-yellowy-white, smooth and creamy, with hoppy layers of strawberry pineapple smoothie, basil flowers, and pear. Finishes with those white frosting vibes that we can’t get enough of. $20 per 4pack. Limit 4pp
